                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Rockhill</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1901-04-08">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 8, 1901</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>(Mr. Rockhill reports that the Austrian claim for war expenses to May 1 is stated
                    at 13,200,000 crowns; 520,000 crowns additional for each month thereafter.
                    Private claims about 21,000 taels.</p>
                <p>He is unofficially informed that Russia will demand, inclusive of railroad
                    claims, £17,500,000. Japan will ask 45,000,000 yen. France will ask 280,000,000
                    francs. Belgium, 30,000,000 francs.</p>
                <p>He will, until otherwise instructed, insist upon scaling, but does not believe it
                    will be agreed to.)</p>
            </div>
        </body>
